Sitting in southwest China's Sichuan Province, Zogye wetland is often associate with the hardest days for the Red Army during the Long March since it is characterized with high altitude, low oxygen and an abundance of swamps. The environment may not be suitable for humans, but the pristine wetland is home to countless wildlife such as black-necked cranes and wolves. Check out the video to learn more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Aba series: Located on the southeastern edge of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Aba Prefecture is rich inÂ diverse ecosystems, such as forests, grasslands, wetlands and glaciers. Stay tuned and explore this hidden land. More on the Aba series: Aba Series | Episode 1: Dagu glacier Aba Series | Episode 3: Baby cranes Aba Series | Episode 4: Fairy lake (Cover image a screenshot from the video) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)